  "prompt": "How can I reach Infosys Pocharam campus from Ameerpet?",
  "response": "To reach Infosys Pocharam campus from Ameerpet, you have several options:\n\n### By Car/Taxi:\n- **Route:** You can take the Inner Ring Road or NH 65 to the Infosys Pocharam campus.\n- **Duration:** It typically takes around 40-60 minutes, depending on traffic conditions.\n\n### By Public Transport:\n- **Option 1: Metro and Bus Combination**\n  - **Step 1:** Take the Hyderabad Metro from Ameerpet Metro Station to Uppal Metro Station. The Blue Line serves this route.\n  - **Step 2:** From Uppal, you can catch a local bus heading towards Pocharam or Ghatkesar. Ask specifically for buses that stop near the Infosys campus.\n  \n- **Option 2: Direct Bus**\n  - You can catch a direct bus from Ameerpet to Pocharam. APSRTC buses or other local buses like 3H/270 will serve this route, but checking the latest timetable and availability is recommended.\n\n### By Auto-rickshaw:\n- **Route:** You can hire an auto-rickshaw from Ameerpet directly to Infosys Pocharam. Negotiate the fare prior to the trip.\n- **Duration:** This might take slightly longer due to frequent traffic stops, approximately 60-80 minutes.\n\n### By Ride-sharing:\n- **Services like Ola or Uber:** Book a ride from your location directly to Infosys Pocharam. This is a convenient option but can vary in cost depending on surge pricing and traffic conditions.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Timing:** Plan your journey taking into consideration peak traffic hours in Hyderabad, which can significantly increase travel time.\n- **Navigation:** Use mapping services like Google Maps for real-time traffic updates and route suggestions.\n- **Safety:** Ensure you're aware of the route and travel safely, especially if taking late-night trips.\n\nMake sure to verify current timings and routes via official sources or apps as public transport options can change.",
